      <br />
      <center><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#792022"><tr><td>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="8" bgcolor="#A0332E"><tr><td>
<font class="pn-title">Hierarchy</font><br /><br /><font class="pn-normal">(1617 total words in this text)</font><br /><font class="pn-normal">(37 Reads)</font> &nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="pn-normal" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=Sections&amp;file=index&amp;req=printpage&amp;artid=8"><img src="modules/Sections/images/print.gif" border="0" Alt="Printer friendly page"></a></font><br /><br /><font class="pn-normal">Here you will find descriptions of the Hierarchy and inforamtion on Rank Ascension.  For a list of who is what - please visit our Roster page.  

<b>Hierarchy</b>
Elders <br>
(For a list of who is what - visit our Roster)<br>
<br>
The Flamekeepers of Norrath currently are run by a council of Elders referred to as the Triumvirate. No one has power over any other. No one sits higher then any other. Our law dictates that in a time of an Elder vote, majority prevails. <br>
<br>
Advisors <br>
Advisors are found in rank just under that of Elders and are considered Officers in the lands of Norrath. Advisors interact and assist directly with the Officers in guild matters and are reported to directly by Knights and Cavaliers. 
<br>
Knights <br>
<br>
Knights hold the highest non-officer position in the guild. At this time, the Knights share the duty of Scout with Cavaliers. Knights will hold more responsibility in the near future once the Scouts prove themselves as an efficient force. Knights report directly to the Advisors with guild matters. <br>
<br>
Cavaliers <br>
Cavaliers hold the first rank of ascension from Initiate. However, in this beginning, responsibility is also given. Along with Knights, they make up the Scout Corps. They also hold a responsibility to assisting Devvon in her responsibilities of working with Seekers. <br>
<br>
Initiate <br>
Initiates make up the bread and butter of the Flamekeepers of Norrath. Upon completing their initiations as Seekers, the individual becomes a full fledged member of the Flamekeepers of Norrath and are given the title Initiate. Initiate's only responsibility is to understand and follow the rules of the guild at all time and to assist in times of need, and when possible, any guildmate. 

<br>
<br>
Seeker <br>
Seekers are those that are walking the path to becoming a Flamekeeper of Norrath. Their walk is both a test for all parties involved as the Seeker sees whether or not the Flamekeepers is for him and her and vice versa. Their time as Seekers is spent learning the guild law as well as joining and sharing time with current Flamekeepers of Norrath. 
<br>
<br>
Special Units <br>
<br>
Torchlighters <br>
Torchlighters are hand picked individuals whose purpose is to prepare fellow guild members for the higher level raiding that will come. They train under, and utilize rules and protocol developed for the Burning Flame Alliance unless they have specific rules that override this. Torchlighters arrange and run raids into various locales for this younger BFA corp (Commonly referred to as JV BFA) as well as events and fun times for the same. <br>
<br>
Scouts <br>
Scouts are a combined unit of all Cavaliers and Knights of the Flamekeepers of Norrath. Their task is to conduct minor research into specific raiding locales, quests or special item drops and report these findings to the Torchlighters. They do not plan and run raids, although this process could be considered a preparation for a Scout to move into the position of Torchlighter, someday. <br>
<br>
<b>Rank Ascension</b><br>
<br>
Elder <br>
Should a time come that one or more Elders feel the need to step down, it will be determined by the remaining Elder Council if replacements will be needed based upon whether or not the Council can handle the responsibilities of the Flamekeepers of Norrath with the current number of Elders. <br>
<br>
Should it be determined that one or more Elder positions are available to be filled, the matter will be brought to the remainder of the guild family. At this time, those with the interest in assuming the title of Elder will be permitted to state just this. Soon thereafter, the guild as a whole will be asked to vote upon who to offer the title of Elder to. 75% of the guild must vote, and of that, one must receive 66% of the votes to be offered the title of Elder. Exceptions and adjustments can be made to these rulings, but they must be based upon a majority vote by the Guild. <br>
<br>
Advisor <br>
The title of &quot;Advisor&quot; is an Officer position as outlined by Everquest and the Flamekeepers of Norrath. This position is not a quested position as are the Knights and Cavaliers. <br>
<br>
To become an Advisor, one must move through the ranks of Seeker, Apprentice, Keeper, Cavalier and Knight (On extremely rare and special occasions, one might be appointed as an Advisor after careful consideration of the Elder Council independant of these steps). Upon obtaining the title of Knight, one may, at any time, send a message to the Elders that they would be willing to undertake the position of Advisor. This is only a notification to the Elders that one is willing, nothing more, and is kept in the Elder records. If the time comes that the Elder Council feels that the need for an Advisor to be added to the ranks has come, then they will look into who has such an interest and they will discuss further action from there. <br>
<br>
This is a position of responsibility and as such, is not something that requires a test such as a quest. The individual will be judged on contributions to the Flamekeepers of Norrath as well as other merits. <br>
<br>
Knight <br>
To obtain the title, &quot;Knight&quot;, within the Flamekeepers of Norrath, the prospective Knight will go through the same process as outlined in the Cavalier quest. It is expected and required, however, that the quest be of a more difficult nature to reflect the upward movement through the ranks. As with the Cavalier quests, a Knight also undergoes a Title and Named Title quest. 
<br><br>
The title of Knight is a two stage process: Title and Named Title. To gain the title of Knight, one must create a quest or grand event and submit this idea to the Elders. Together, the Elders and questor will look at the quest and modify any portion of it that might need it. Successful completion of this quest will grant upon the questor the title, Knight. <br>
<br>
The Named Title portion of the process will involve the Elders and the prospective Knight working together to devise some goal or culmination of the Knight quest. Upon successful completion of the Named Title portion of the quest, the prospective Knight will choose a title that they wish to go along with the Knight rank. 
<br>
<br>
Example: For his Knight quest, Orukal and Devvon chose to run a raid in South Karana with specific, named creatures as their targets. In working with the Guild Elders, it was arranged that their Named Knight quest would be the successful victory over one &quot;Minor&quot; named creature and one &quot;Major&quot; named creature. Upon completion of the first portion of the quest, Orukal and Devvon both became Knights. Upon completion of the second portion of the quest, Orukal chose the title, &quot;Knight Tracker&quot; and Devvon chose the title, &quot;Knight of Surefall&quot;. <br>
<br>
Cavalier <br>
Some Keepers will feel the need to contribute more to the Flamekeepers of Norrath and will seek avenues to do just that. The title of Cavalier fills this desire and is a quested for position. <br>
<br>
The title of Cavalier is a two stage process: Title and Named Title. To gain the title of Cavalier, one must create a quest or grand event and submit this idea to the Elders. Together, the Elders and questor will look at the quest and modify any portion of it that might need it. Successful completion of this quest will grant upon the questor the title, Cavalier. <br>
<br>
The Named Title portion of the process will involve the Elders and the prospective Cavalier working together to devise some goal or culmination of the Cavalier quest. Upon successful completion of the Named Title portion of the quest, the prospective Cavalier will choose a title that they wish to go along with the Cavalier rank. 
<br>
<br>
Example: For his Cavalier quest, Orukal d'Karr chose to undertake the challenge of crafting the Trueshot Bow. In working with the Guild Elders, it was arranged that his Named Cavalier quest would be to craft a second such bow and offer it to a young Ranger of Norrath. Upon completion of the first portion of the quest, Orukal became a Cavalier. Upon completion of the second portion of the quest, Orukal chose the title &quot;Cavalier Tracker&quot;. <br>
<br>
Keeper <br>
At the end of 90 day period as an Apprentice, you will be promoted to &quot;Keeper&quot; and a ceremony will be held at the next guild meeting you attend to honor you. The Keepers are the core and heart of the Flamekeepers of Norrath. <br>
<br>
Apprentice <br>
Once you have obtained 3 letters of support, you will be tagged as an &quot;Apprentice&quot; for 90 days. This is a period of mutual &quot;meshing&quot;. During this time you will also be given two quests to complete, as a show of loyalty. These are based on class and level. You can complete your quests early but this will not speed up your status. The Apprentice period is a mandatory 90 days. <br>
<br>
Seeker<br>
A Seeker is a prospective member of the Flamekeepers of Norrath. They are those that have shown an interest in joining our guild, and have begun the necessary steps needed to enter our fold. Prior to receiving their guild tag, a Seeker must fulfill the following criteria: <br>
<br>
They must be level 20. <br>
All races, classes, alignments welcome. <br>
They must post interest/intent in the Flamekeepers of Norrath's Seekers Forum. <br>
They must obtain 3 letters of support from current Keepers (Elders and Seekers cannot write these letters.). <br>
A prospective Seeker that bears the tag of another Guild must remove him or herself from that guild for a period of no less then 5 days before any letters of support will be accepted. &quot;Trying out&quot; the Flamekeepers of Norrath while still tagged by another guild is considered bad form and the Seeker process will not begin.<br>

